 Juris Doctor (J.D.) and admitted to at least one state bar (or equivalent) 
 2+ years of post-admission legal experience 
 Exceptional written and verbal communication skills 
 
Amazon's Legal Department is looking for a talented attorney to support Amazon Web Services (AWS), a dynamic and rapidly growing business within Amazon.com that is at the forefront of the cloud computing industry. AWS provides its customers with IT infrastructure services ranging from on-demand compute, storage, database, and network and content delivery, to artificial intelligence, mobile, internet of things, and more.
 
As Associate Corporate Counsel, you will partner with AWS Support and Managed Services business teams to develop, launch and support AWS services worldwide. You will serve as one of the primary lawyers responsible for counseling the AWS Support and Managed Services business teams on a broad range of product, commercial, technology, privacy, and regulatory matters, as well as structuring, drafting, and negotiating commercial transactions. You will work directly with the business, providing day-to-day advice, serving as lead counsel for strategic deals and relationships, and setting up structural solutions that enable clients to achieve their business objectives as efficiently as possible. The role also includes participating in other Amazon-wide legal projects, including managing legal issues that arise in existing commercial relationships and handling regulatory compliance and civil litigation issues and inquiries.
 
The successful candidate must be inquisitive, enthusiastic about technology, enjoy working hard and being continually challenged, and demonstrate independent sound judgment even in ambiguous situations. Compensation is based on experience and includes equity compensation.
 
 
 Familiarity with cloud computing regulations 
 Familiarity with privacy regulations 
 Familiarity with MSP/MSSP regulations 
 Familiarity with web services/cloud computing 
 Sound and practical business judgment 
 An ability to manage a large number and variety of critical projects, often in ambiguous environments 
 An ability to work both independently and as part of a cross-functional team 
 
